@Nimble is correct in saying all this could be done with path-planner. Don’t try to reinvent the wheel, that’s literally the point of coding libraries and developed applications.

In order to be flexible, you have to know you can do flexible correctly every time no matter what. You will want to design a very robust auto system that you don’t ever have to test. This is a difficult problem to solve because it is often more advantageous to create 2-3 really quick autos that you spend lots of time tuning than an unlimited supply of slower ones.

We are starting to experiment with on-the-fly auto making, and it starts with creating a discipline approach that will guarantee that we can do something like that in the heat of the moment. It’s a lot of work, but can be done. It’s your job to prove to yourself that it can be done every single time no matter what.
